Bouchard and Soler-Espinosa broke each other twice in a first set that lasted 44 minutes.

But Bouchard proved too strong for the Spaniard in the second set and needed just 22 minutes to close out the victory.

Bouchard, who won junior Wimbledon in 2012, will play Germany's Andrea Petkovic in the third round.

